  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/experimental/l2geth/core/state_transition.go#L219-L279\r\n\r\nCaution: Because of the async between rollup_service and the  chain, the rollup's validating result may not correct.\r\nSo,  this logic is short of checking value transfer failure before actually going to EVM，which is inconsistent with \"The first balance may never fail\":.What's more, no matter what the result is of this tx, the miner should always be rewarded with fee which is already paid by sender by \"buyGas\".\r\n\r\n",
